gender, class, post-structuralism, and new historicism. The range and intellectual energy of the essays collected here give the reader a new sense of London’s richness and variety, especially his treatment of diverse cultures. Having in the past focused more on London’s personal “world,” we are now afforded an opportunity to look more closely at his art and the numerous worlds it uncovers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh1 aAuerbach, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaskett, Sam S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerkove, Lawrence I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCassuto, Leonard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCassuto, Leonard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCrow, Charles L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDerrick, Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFurer, Andrew J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGair, Christopher Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLabor, Earle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeluso, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReesman, Jeanne Campbell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReesman, Jeanne Campbell, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShor, Francis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSlagel, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStasz, Clarice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voc